# Security Rules

> Extends [root AGENTS.md](../AGENTS.md). Cross-cutting — load when working on auth, input handling, secrets, or rendering.

## Always

- Load secrets from environment variables or GCP Secret Manager. [MUST]
- Extract `locationId` server-side from JWT/auth context only. [MUST]
- Sanitize with `DOMPurify.sanitize()` before any `v-html` or `innerHTML` assignment. [MUST]
- Apply CSRF protection on all state-changing HTTP endpoints. [MUST]
- Use IAM v2 (`@platform-core/iam-v2`) guards or helper methods on protected routes. [MUST]
- Validate and strip unknown fields on all incoming API payloads (via class-validator). [MUST]
- Rotate exposed secrets immediately and audit for similar patterns in codebase. [MUST]

## Never

- Never hardcode API keys, passwords, tokens, or private keys in source code. [MUST]
- Never trust `locationId` from client request body, query, or params. [MUST]
- Never use `v-html` without DOMPurify sanitization. [MUST]
- Never expose stack traces or internal error details in API responses. [SHOULD]
- Never log PII (email, phone, name) in structured logs. [SHOULD]

## Prefer

- Prefer `unknown` over `any` for externally typed data — validate before use.
- Prefer explicit allow-lists for CORS origins over wildcards.
- Prefer short-lived tokens with refresh over long-lived tokens.
- Prefer HTTPS-only cookies with `HttpOnly` and `SameSite=Strict` for session tokens.

## Verify

- Confirm no hardcoded secrets in changed files (`.env` values, inline strings).
- Confirm all new routes have appropriate IAM guard applied.
- Confirm user-supplied content is sanitized before HTML rendering.

